## API Documentation: POST /api/import-entries

### Overview
Robust endpoint for importing rejection and rework entries from CSV/Excel data. Handles messy, real-world data with automatic normalization, flexible column matching, and fallback entity creation.

### Authentication
**Required:** Admin role (checked via `isAdmin` middleware)

### Request

#### HTTP Method & Path
```
POST /api/import-entries
```

#### Headers
```
Content-Type: application/json
```

#### Body Schema
```typescript
{
  rows: Array<Record<string, any>>,  // Array of objects (rows from CSV/Excel)
  dryRun?: boolean                    // Optional: true to preview without inserting (default: false)
}
```

#### Request Example
```json
{
  "rows": [
    {
      "Date": "2024-03-15",
      "Part Number": "Widget X1",
      "Type": "Rejection",
      "Code": "SURF-001",
      "Purpose": "Surface Defect",
      "Zone": "Assembly",
      "Quantity": "5",
      "Remarks": "Minor scratches found"
    },
    {
      "date": "2024-03-16",
      "part_number": "Widget X2",
      "type": "rework",
      "code": "ELEC-002",
      "purpose": "Electrical Retest",
      "zone": "QA",
      "qty": "3",
      "notes": "Power supply test failed"
    }
  ],
  "dryRun": false
}
```

